          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>ABLE to Work Act of 201</strong><b>7</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code, with respect to ABLE accounts (tax-exempt savings accounts for persons with a disability), to allow: (1) an ABLE account beneficiary to make additional contributions to an ABLE account equal to the lesser of such beneficiary's compensation or an amount equal to the federal poverty line for a one-person household, and (2) a retirement savings tax credit for contributions to an ABLE account. </p>]]></text>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <actionDate>2017-04-04</actionDate>
